ccessful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Brenchley was born in 1350, in Brenchley, Kent, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 3 sons with Joan Battisford. He died on 26 May 1406, in his hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1350–26 May 1406":"1350–26. mai 1406","1366–1453":"1366–1453","1375–1446":"1375–1446","1385–1453":"1385–1453","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1350–1406":"1350–1406","26 May 1406":"26. mai 1406","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1366":"1366","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","about 1385":"umbes 1385","about 1375":"umbes 1375","1406":"1406","Brenchley, Kent, England":"Brenchley, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fi":{"1350–26 May 1406":"1350–26. toukokuuta 1406","1366–1453":"1366–1453","1375–1446":"1375–1446","1385–1453":"1385–1453","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1350–1406":"1350–1406","26 May 1406":"26. toukokuuta 1406","1385":"1385","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Abt 1400":"noin 1400","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1366":"1366","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","about 1385":"noin 1385","about 1375":"noin 1375","1406":"1406","Brenchley, Kent, England":"Brenchley, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fr":{"1350–26 May 1406":"1350–26 mai 1406","1366–1453":"1366–1453","1375–1446":"1375–1446","1385–1453":"1385–1453","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1350–1406":"1350–1406",